-- Pimco Total Return Fund drops U.S. gov't-related holdings to 45 pct
-- 
-- Mon Aug 11, 2014 06:39PM EDT
-- None



Aug 11 (Reuters) - The Pimco Total Return Fund, overseen by Bill Gross, slightly decreased its U.S. government-related holdings for a second straight month in July to 45 percent from 47 percent in June, Pimco's website said on Monday.

The Pimco Total Return Fund also reduced its mortgage holdings in July to 20 percent, down from 22 percent in June, Pimco added. Pimco Total Return Fund's money market and net cash equivalents exposure stood at negative 8 percent in July, from negative 11 percent in June, the Newport Beach, California bond firm said.